    "overview_number": 2,
    "overview_title": "Walk the Line",
    "overview_subtitle": "Adding Integers, Part I",
    "overview_description": "In this lesson, students walk a number line to demonstrate the addition of integers as they interpret an integer's absolute value as the distance moved in either direction. They use a number line to add integers or identify an unknown addend in a number sentence. Students recognize that they can apply their rules to rational numbers and also write number sentences that sum to zero."
  },
